Hamon: “Let me get this straight. You want me to help distribute illicit drugs—Grade 3 drugs mind you—because you need information?”
<<show_character Backend 0 General>>
Matthias: “Indeed. The specifics are on a need-to-know basis of which you do not have the clearance. Just know that if you agree to this, we will overlook all your past failings. You can continue running your department as you have been as long as you agree.”
<<show_character Backend 1 Hamon>>
Hamon: “Blackmail, eh?”
<<show_character Backend 0 General>>
Matthias: “It’s the government, Julius. Quid pro quo. You do this for me, I’ll help you, because one day, someone else will decide to look into why Quadrant 1 has such a low conviction rate.”
<<show_character Backend 1 Hamon>>
He sighs.
Hamon: “Fine. How is this going to work?”
<<show_character Backend 0 General>>
Matthias: “It’s simple, you’ll meet with a representative and the two of you will find a way to distribute the product. How you do it does not matter, just as long as you succeed.”
<<show_character Backend 1 Hamon>>
Hamon: “Is that it?”
<<show_character Backend 0 General>>
Matthias: “That’s it. But before you leave, we’ll need to keep this meeting between us. I’m sure you understand.”
<<show_character Backend 1 Hamon>>
Hamon: “Fine.”
<<show_character Backend 0 General>>
Matthias: “Good. Lieutenant? Escort Mr. Hamon to the medical ward. They already have their instructions.”
